the gnome tumbing off in the opposite direction.. <br><br>The Shadowknight class is populated with characters like the Kurgen from Highlander, and a preponderance of wicked Dark Elves, whose evil and treachery are legendary. What place do gnomes have in that world? In a pen&amp;paper version of EQ, true shadowknights would capture these little walking jokes and use them as court jesters or bait for monsters.<br><br>You could argue, and say &quot;well at level 60 you will think twice about laughing at my gnome SK&quot;. I am speaking in terms of the overall campaign scenario in a RP sense, and this doesn't apply - I am suggesting that gnome SKs would never make it to that level. <br>The only reason they will is because in a computer RPG, you can never be caught sleeping, or with your armor off, nor is pvp available on the servers where these characters will predominantly reside. <br><br>I'm not going to quit EQ over this or anything, I just think it is a very silly thing to do, on the part of the developers. It tells me that the original vision of EQ has most certainly changed.<br><br>Do you agree or disagree with this perception of the Gnome SK? Thoughts/comments?<br><br>~Cykranosh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ualdrickfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AldrickFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/14/02 1:20:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1540.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh, come on! </span><hr size=1> I think &quot;Mini-me&quot; was a gnome shadowknight <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Aldrick <p></p><i></i></td></tr