owever, much of the &quot;dark knight&quot; class is about inspiring fear in your enemies, crushing them under your unholy might, etc.  I too have a hard time picturing gnomes ever being able to work up that kind of awe in people.  I couldn't picture a gnome shadowknight bossing around an army of orcs and trolls and ogres, but I could see that with any of the other races that can play Shadowknight.<br><br>Evil gnomes always seemed like they'd be more tricksterish, kind of like evil leprechauns n such.  The straightforward menace of Shadowknights just seemed a bit beyond gnomes.<br><br>All in all, however, I don't really care too much.  If someone wants to play a gnome SK, let 'em, and I can just be really impressed if they're convincing, and mock them mercilessly if they're not <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Aldrick <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeiht.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feiht</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/14/02 2:28:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1540.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh, come on! </span><hr size=1> Halfling ranger makes sense but so does a Halfling Bard.  Their clerics follow Bristlebane and the disposition fits a Bristlebane Bard IMO. <p>Feiht<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85386>Profile</a><BR><BR>Muso<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97550>Profile</a><BR><BR><a href=http://www.lamer.net/guesswhat.jpg>Guess what?</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://