d User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/14/02 3:28:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1540.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh, come on! </span><hr size=1> I agree that allowing any race to be any class would be neat. It would give those that have done everything (you know, those uber players that have like 10 50+ chars on 3 different accounts) a little more of a challenge.<br><br>Plus, I have always liked playing oddball class/race combos.. just for something to muck around with... if nothing else it could prove to be an interesting RP experience <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaberianthebrave.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aberian the Brave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/14/02 3:41:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1540.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh, come on! </span><hr size=1> okay wait.. now though this doesnt REALLy fit, as this character was a Rogue not a SK... <br>PEN and paper too... I played in an RPGA tourney one time, where there was a Halfling Rogue with Intimidation... on a skill roll he Successfully Indimidated a Storm Giant.. now DM rolled a 20.. wasnt much he can do about that... NOW THAT would have been Hilarious to see...<br><br>but that is kind of the point here.. it would be comical to see a halfling or a gnome trying to be dark sinister overpowering Dark Lords of Battle.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>but if a Halfling can Indimidate a Storm Giant, I guess Homer the Gnome could TRY to be the next Lord of Darkness<br><br><br>Aberian the Brave<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/14/02 5:55:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1540.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lunarpages.com/maladominus/exhibit/trollfood.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh, come on! </span><hr size=1> Gnome Shadow Knights was an easy thing to add for Verant.  Gnomes already worship a Death God called Bertoxxulous.  This is why many Gnome players choose the profession of Necromancer because it is the second best Necromancer in the game in stats (naked character generation stats) after Erudite necros. <br><br>Gnomes already can be:  <br><br>1) The Warrior Class<br><br>and<br><br>2) The Necromancer Class <br><br>What do you get when you mix Warrior plus Necromancer?  Uhhhhh.... you get Shadow Knight. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/14/02 6:05:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1540.to