at &quot;well, they'd sure be unique.&quot;  'RPG uniqueness' is so overdone that it's downright conformist.  The singlemost unique thing a roleplayer can do, in the current roleplaying environment (not just EQ, but all over the place), is play a fairly standard character.<br><br>In fact, sometimes this is what makes a character compelling.  For example, Paksennarion, from Elizabeth Moon's &quot;The Deed of Paksennarion&quot; series, is an extremely compelling character because she's a very typical paladin.  That's very rarely done (in favor of the horde of Drizz't wannabees).<br><br>Lasgalen Lothir<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukelisk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, YOU'RE evil</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/14/02 8:28:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1540.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://216.40.201.155/s/games/ultima/MON16.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh, come on! </span><hr size=1> You wouldn't see another Iksar class unless there was a damned good reason (Personally, I think they should have RANGERS goddammit, it makes SENSE!), because the other magics are forbidden among the Iksar race. That's why they have necromancers, but no mage/chanter/wizzies. <p><img src="http://publish.hometown.aol.com/bseh42/images/kelsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboar